posts.description:
Hey best friendüëã
.
Thanks for driving for 12 hours to bring me a car, help me pack/move, and, you know, the eight and a half years of friendship.

Being a part of a recovery community always terrified me, in part because I knew that I was surrounding myself around a group of people that I was statistically more likely to lose. Yoga was easy in that sense, if someone didn‚Äôt show up to class for a couple of weeks, you maybe assumed that they were trying out something else or on vacation, or at the worst they were moving away from the practice a bit as part of their journey. But when I connected into recovery communities, the fear associated with someone being missing was so much more real, and last night was another night of a worst case scenario.
.
To make a list of the people who I‚Äôve lost, would be a near impossible task, but this was the first where I felt the hit right to the middle of my chosen family. That chosen family that I used to be so scared of being a part of, that now I can‚Äôt imagine a life without. I woke up crying every couple of hours last night feeling the weight of so many hurting hearts, and today everything feels so fucking heavy but I know that this is a part of the process. To hold space for the ones who don‚Äôt make it, and to remember why it is that we do the work that we do.
.
Rest easy, Eliah, you will forever be so loved by so many.

My last day of work, and it‚Äôs a loving farewell to @sajewellness!
.
This has been such an amazing team to be a part of, and I‚Äôm so grateful for the love and support that I‚Äôve received here.
.
So, now it really feels like this is all happening, and the excitement for this next chapter is coming in full force. üíö

10 days out from our move and it's the 4 P's. Packing, Procrastination, Puppies, and Pizza.
.
Also, I haven't done laundry in way longer than I care to admit and as usual @meundies delivered early to save the day. But Ash isn't home, so Charlie gets a cape, and I get to add to my laundry pile. üíÅüôàü•áüçï

Time suddenly feels like it's moving so quickly... Tomorrow is my last day of work, next week is all packing, and then we're off on our adventure.
.
Last night was spent around my chosen family, and I had my first pang of feeling sad about leaving, which was quickly replaced with gratitude for all the people who have made this city feel like home, and knowing that moving nine hours away doesn't make those people any less my family. #11daystogo

New home decorüåø
.
Every big life shift I've marked with a tattoo, a reminder of what it feels like to move from the heart. This time it's marked with a small sprig of lavender, and I'm feeling all kinds of happy.

PNW living‚úåÔ∏è
.
We came for two days, and the dogs are exhausted, we desperately need showers, but we found a home (with running water and electricity) so this is all happening and it feels so damn good.

Eight months ago I was on this beach, sending Ash photos trying to convince them that moving out here was the best idea ever, after being here for less than a day. And now I'm back out here, this time with our pup and looking for a house for us all to live in.
.
So excited to call this place home üíöüå≤

We're taking our day dreams off the shelf, and letting them run free.
.
In one month it's 'goodbye' to Vancouver, and 'hello' to quiet mountain life in the West Kootenays. I honestly have no idea what life is going to look like, and when I think about all the unknowns it starts to feel a bit scary, but right now it's one foot in front of the other with full faith that every step is taking me in the direction I'm meant to go. üíöüå≤
